      <hedline>
        <hl1>National Briefing | Southwest: New Mexico: Chemical And Atomic Waste Cleanup</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Steve Barnes (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Barnes, Steve</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Energy Dept pledges to spend $2.4 million this year to clean up chemical and atomic waste at 126 sites at Sandia National Laboratories in Albuquerque, NM (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Department of Energy pledged spending of $2.4 million this year to clean up chemical and atomic waste at 126 sites at Sandia National Laboratories in Albuquerque. Some of the contamination, which dates to 1945, has entered the underground aquifer that serves Albuquerque, although the state said the city's water was being drawn from untainted wells and was safe.</p>
        <p>Steve Barnes (NYT)</p>
      </block>
